{
  "texts": [
    "For the acquisition of representative images, we used an Andor Dragonfly Spinning Disk Confocal Microscope (OXFORD Instruments, England) mounted on a Leica DMi8 microscope stand, equipped with an HC PL APO 100×/1.40 OIL CS2 Leica objective.",
    "The pinhole size was set to 40 µm.",
    "The camera was a Zyla Plus 4.2MP sCMOS with 2048 × 2048 pixels, with an effective pixel size of 0.063 µm.",
    "A piezoelectric Z stage was used to acquire Z stacks at 0.2 µm intervals.",
    "Excitation lasers were 405 nm (for DAPI), 488 nm (for Alexa Fluor 488), and 561 nm (for Alexa Fluor 555)."
  ]
}